'''Nahuel Molina Lucero''' (born 6 April 1998) is an Argentine professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
Molina trained in the Barça Juniors Luján sports project, a [[FC Barcelona]] project in [[Argentina]],<ref>{{cite web |title=FC Barcelona Juniors Luján |url=https://arxiu.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/futbol/futbol_base/especials/fcb_argentina/continguts/Projecte.html|website=FC Barcelona archive|access-date=5 December 2023}}</ref> which even led him to travel to [[Barcelona]] to train with the lower sections of FC Barcelona. In 2012, the Juniors Luján project was integrated into the youth ranks of [[CA Boca Juniors]], and Molina continued his training in this club.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Los inicios culés de Nahuel Molina detallados por su descubridor|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/inicios-cules-nahuel-molina-detallados-95370344|website=Sport España|date=3 December 2023|access-date=5 December 2023|language=es}}</ref>

On 18 February 2016, he made his first team debut for Boca Juniors in a league game against [[San Martín de San Juan]], playing the full game.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/02/18/argentina/primera-division/ca-san-martin-de-san-juan/boca-juniors/2182932/|title=San Martín San Juan vs. Boca Junior|website=Soccerway|date=18 February 2016|access-date=20 February 2016}}</ref><ref>https://historiadeboca.com.ar/jugadores/nahuel-molina-lucero/1203/1905/2018/1.html Historia de Boca.com.ar Nahuel Molina Lucero</ref> In January 2018, Molina was loaned out to [[Defensa y Justicia]] for the rest of the year.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Molina deja Boca por Defensa y Justicia|url=https://es.besoccer.com/noticia/molina-deja-boca-por-defensa-y-justicia-359225|website=BeSoccer|date=11 January 2018|access-date=1 June 2024|language=es}}</ref>

On 15 September 2020, Molina joined [[Udinese Calcio]] on a free transfer until 2025.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Official: Molina joins Udinese|url=https://www.football-italia.net/158582/official-molina-joins-udinese|website=Football Italia |date=15 September 2020 }}</ref> On 28 July 2022, he joined [[Atlético Madrid]] on a five-year contract,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Welcome, Nahuel Molina! |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/molina-is-now-a-red-white-player |website=Atlético Madrid|date=28 July 2022}}</ref> for a reported fee of €10 million and €5 million in variables.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Pablo|last=Egea|title=Nahuel Molina es nuevo jugador del Atlético |trans-title=Nahuel Molina is a new Atletico player |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2022/07/28/62d1960b268e3efd1d8b45c3.html |website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|date=28 July 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Nahuel Molina WC2022.jpg|left|thumb|237x237px|Molina playing for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
On 3 June 2021, Molina debuted for the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]] in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Chile national football team|Chile]], coming as a substitute to [[Juan Foyth]] in the 81st minute.<ref>{{Cite news|title=La historia de Nahuel Molina Lucero: de quedar libre en Boca a la Selección Argentina|url=https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/seleccion-argentina-copa-america-molina-lucero-libre-boca-sorpresa--id350612.html|website=[[TyC Sports]]|date=14 October 2021|language=es}}</ref>

In the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] quarter-final match against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] on 9 December 2022, Molina scored his first goal for Argentina, starting in six matches for Argentina as first choice right back scoring one goal and providing one assist throughout the tournament en route to become champions.<ref>{{cite web|first=Phil|last=McNulty|title=World Cup 2022: Argentina beat the Netherlands in penalty shootout to reach semi-finals|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63830319|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=9 December 2022|access-date=10 December 2022}}</ref>

In June 2024, Molina was included in Lionel Scaloni's final 26-man Argentina squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=Todo Noticias}}</ref>
